# SNPE C++ Inference — Build & Run Instructions
#
# Auto-generated by QUAD (Qualcomm Unified Agent for Developers)
# Model: {{ model_path }}
# Runtime: {{ runtime | default('cpu') }}

## Prerequisites

- QAIRT SDK installed (`source activate.sh`)
- CMake 3.14+
- C++17 compiler (clang++ or g++)

## Build (Host — x86_64 Linux)

```bash
mkdir build && cd build
cmake .. -DTARGET_ARCH=x86_64-linux-clang
cmake --build .
```

## Build (Cross-compile — aarch64 Linux)

```bash
mkdir build && cd build
cmake .. \
    -DCMAKE_CXX_COMPILER=aarch64-linux-gnu-g++ \
    -DTARGET_ARCH=aarch64-oe-linux-gcc11.2
cmake --build .
```

## Build (Android — via NDK)

```bash
cd $SNPE_ROOT/examples/SNPE/NativeCpp/SampleCode_CPP
ndk-build NDK_TOOLCHAIN_VERSION=clang APP_STL=c++_static \
    NDK_PROJECT_PATH=. NDK_APPLICATION_MK=Application.mk APP_BUILD_SCRIPT=Android.mk
```

## Run (Local)

```bash
./inference {{ model_path }} input_list.txt ./output
```

## Run (on Target Device via QUAD)

```bash
# Deploy and execute in one command
cd /path/to/QUAD
./deploy.sh {{ model_path }} --runtime {{ runtime | default('cpu') }}
```

## Input Format

Create `input_list.txt` with one raw file path per line:
```
input_0.raw
input_1.raw
```

Each `.raw` file should contain float32 tensor data in NHWC format.

## Output

Results saved to `./output/Result_N/<tensor_name>.raw` (float32 binary).
